<i> the same struggles.</i>

00:43.944 --> 00:45.511
<i> Well, if there's any last</i>
<i> clues of anything,</i>

00:45.513 --> 00:46.311
<i> It's gonna be in here.</i>

00:49.850 --> 00:51.050
Oh, wow.

00:52.353 --> 00:53.352
Yeah!

00:53.421 --> 00:54.319
Boom!

00:54.321 --> 00:56.588
<i> I am captain josh harris.</i>

00:56.590 --> 00:57.923
I keep looking in that picture

00:57.925 --> 00:59.725
And he keeps looking back
at me.

00:59.727 --> 01:01.427
<i> Phil harris was my father,</i>

01:01.429 --> 01:03.562
<i> And a legend</i>
<i> on the bering sea.</i>

01:04.131 --> 01:05.798
[phil] <i> I'm a sweetheart.</i>

01:05.800 --> 01:07.633
<i> You can't get</i>
<i> any better than me.</i>

01:07.701 --> 01:10.035
I'm just a smiling
[bleep] jack.

01:10.104 --> 01:13.038
Three, two, one!

01:13.040 --> 01:14.940
[man] go, go,
go, go, go, go, go!

01:15.009 --> 01:16.842
[narrator] <i> now,</i>
<i> both casey and jeff</i>

01:16.911 --> 01:18.310
<i> Deliver to clients in hawaii</i>

01:19.013 --> 01:20.612
[jeff] ooh.

01:20.614 --> 01:23.115
[narrator] <i> shane and I</i>
<i> are hitting the road,</i>

01:23.117 --> 01:24.550
<i> Looking for clues</i>
<i> from the old man's past</i>

01:24.618 --> 01:26.518
<i> To expand the business.</i>

01:26.520 --> 01:27.753
So I'm going through
my dad's stuff

01:27.822 --> 01:29.288
And I find this paper.

01:29.290 --> 01:34.426
Mag bay is one the hottest
fishing spots going right now.

01:34.428 --> 01:36.128
[narrator] <i> but in order</i>
<i> to make any headway...</i>

01:36.130 --> 01:37.796
[casey] it's gotta be
a marlin.

01:37.798 --> 01:40.799
We're smelling what
we're selling today, guys.

01:40.801 --> 01:42.601
<i> I got to lean</i>
<i> on my dad's old friends.</i>

01:43.537 --> 01:45.304
I would think that
if he was down there,

01:45.306 --> 01:46.705
I bet he was fishing.

01:47.641 --> 01:48.841
[narrator] <i> because time...</i>

01:48.909 --> 01:50.709
[jeff] I feel a shocker
on the bull box,

01:50.711 --> 01:52.244
I don't want this guy
chasing our fish.

01:52.346 --> 01:53.212
<i> Is running out.</i>

01:54.115 --> 01:55.214
[casey] right here
under the boat.

01:55.216 --> 01:56.014
[groans]

02:02.690 --> 02:03.956
[casey] <i> we're on, we're on.</i>

02:04.024 --> 02:06.959
[tense music playing]

02:06.961 --> 02:08.060
I just hooked something,
I don't know,

02:08.129 --> 02:09.761
But it's definitely
something good-sized,

02:09.863 --> 02:11.263
It's taking line.

02:11.332 --> 02:12.898
Oh, yeah.

02:12.900 --> 02:14.600
Looks like jeff might be
hooked up right here.

02:16.036 --> 02:17.136
Get him in, brother!

02:17.905 --> 02:19.938
<i> Losing our mainland clients</i>

02:20.007 --> 02:21.907
It was a big setback,
no doubt.

02:21.909 --> 02:24.309
But we're not the type
of guys that sit around
and cry about it.

02:24.311 --> 02:27.146
<i> So, while josh chases down</i>
<i> leads from phil,</i>

02:27.214 --> 02:28.413
<i> Jeff and I</i>
<i> are gonna catch fish</i>

02:28.415 --> 02:30.115
<i> And find places to sell it.</i>

02:30.117 --> 02:32.718
We got 1,000 pound order
from taylor and his poke shop

02:32.720 --> 02:34.052
But we need more.

02:35.489 --> 02:36.822
[jeff] it's gotta be a fish,
if we can get it,

02:36.824 --> 02:38.023
It's a blessing.

02:38.025 --> 02:39.057
Woo!

02:40.127 --> 02:41.560
It's jumping,
he's got a marlin.

02:41.629 --> 02:42.861
Big one.

02:42.930 --> 02:44.229
By the boat
these guys can be a nightmare,

02:44.231 --> 02:46.932
So you just gotta be
really, really careful.

02:47.001 --> 02:49.234
[tense music playing]

02:49.336 --> 02:50.502
[jeff] I'm trying
to get this fish,

02:50.504 --> 02:52.204
But this fish
is also trying to get me.

02:53.707 --> 02:54.806
Oh, oh, oh, oh.

02:56.043 --> 02:57.209
Nice fish, man.

02:58.245 --> 03:00.212
Oh, we got a little splash
back there.

03:00.915 --> 03:02.514
Get him! Get it!

03:04.118 --> 03:05.717
Decent sized marlin,
that's a lot of work

03:05.719 --> 03:07.052
To get over the rail
by yourself.

03:07.721 --> 03:09.054
He can do it, though.

03:10.224 --> 03:11.423
[jeff] oh, back.

03:11.425 --> 03:13.325
[bleep], I'm gaffing
this [bleep] dude.

03:14.762 --> 03:15.561
Woo.

03:15.662 --> 03:17.963
[tense music playing]

03:21.302 --> 03:22.601
[casey] that's at least
100-pounder.

03:25.940 --> 03:27.406
That'll put a dent in it.

03:27.408 --> 03:28.507
Little nightmares.

03:30.311 --> 03:31.510
Nice fish, though.

03:31.512 --> 03:32.711
I'm happy we got him.

03:35.249 --> 03:36.815
[casey] that looks like
a nice one. How big is it?

03:38.118 --> 03:39.518
I think 110?

03:39.520 --> 03:40.686
-[casey] 110? 120?
-Yeah.

03:40.688 --> 03:42.354
You know, something.

03:42.456 --> 03:45.324
<i> Marlin is highly</i>
<i> sought after locally.</i>

03:45.326 --> 03:47.125
When we ship it
to taylor in kauai,

03:47.127 --> 03:49.828
We could probably get
between $8 to $10 a pound.

03:49.830 --> 03:51.730
<i> I respect what josh is doing</i>

03:51.732 --> 03:53.799
<i> Trying to follow</i>
<i> in the old man's footsteps.</i>

03:53.801 --> 03:55.801
But for me, this market,

03:56.503 --> 03:57.603
This is my home.

03:57.605 --> 04:00.939
[tense music playing]

04:05.412 --> 04:06.511
[shane] yeah,
that's a nice truck.

04:06.513 --> 04:07.713
[josh] yeah.

04:08.349 --> 04:10.148
It's a '53? '52?

04:10.250 --> 04:11.216
[shane] nice.

04:11.852 --> 04:13.719
Something my grandpa restored.

04:14.321 --> 04:15.287
Ooh.

04:17.091 --> 04:18.924
And I'll start taking
a peek at things.

