<i> The notebooks I found</i>
<i> in my grandpa grant's traile</i>

04:23.731 --> 04:26.398
Had fishing spots written down
from all across the globe.

04:26.834 --> 04:27.833
<i> Look at that.</i>

04:29.937 --> 04:32.104
Ports: Westport, new zealand,

04:32.106 --> 04:33.038
Baja,

04:33.607 --> 04:36.408
H & l to nova scotia.

04:36.410 --> 04:38.210
Maybe there's something
in this locker in seattle

04:38.212 --> 04:39.611
That could connect the dots.

04:42.149 --> 04:43.949
Let's take a little peek
at this.

04:45.619 --> 04:46.618
[shane] <i> what'd you find ther</i>

04:46.686 --> 04:48.153
[josh] I don't know.
I'm about to find out.

04:52.126 --> 04:53.425
Oh, wow.

04:54.495 --> 04:57.062
[josh] louisiana,
gulf of mexico.

04:59.133 --> 05:01.233
I mean, he did go down
to mexico to fish,

05:01.802 --> 05:03.201
But that was for fun.

05:03.203 --> 05:05.103
I remember cozumel,
been there a lot.

05:06.307 --> 05:08.006
He bought me a shirt
when I was a kid.

05:08.008 --> 05:09.308
-[laughs]
-from cozumel.

05:09.310 --> 05:11.143
Dad saves all his charts,
doesn't he?

05:11.244 --> 05:12.844
Yeah. That's what
fishermen do.

05:14.214 --> 05:16.214
But we'll keep this.
Put that in the keep pile.

05:16.216 --> 05:17.015
[shane] all right.

05:18.218 --> 05:19.418
[josh] what else have we got?

05:22.222 --> 05:24.723
Port and boatyard slips.

05:24.725 --> 05:26.425
That's where the cornelia
was built.

05:28.128 --> 05:30.729
Mag bay, I think that's short
for magdalena bay.

05:31.932 --> 05:33.598
Baja mexico, right?

05:34.201 --> 05:35.133
[josh] yeah, I think.

05:35.235 --> 05:37.035
[shane] I swear I saw that
in this book.

05:38.906 --> 05:40.105
[josh] baja peninsula?

05:41.408 --> 05:42.407
[shane] it says
it right there.

05:45.512 --> 05:47.112
Okay. The rocks.

05:47.114 --> 05:50.415
I don't know what a lot
of this stuff is, but yeah.

05:51.318 --> 05:52.517
Do you know anything
about mexico?

05:53.554 --> 05:55.220
-Do you?
-I don't,

05:55.222 --> 05:57.222
But I do know somebody
who does.

05:58.525 --> 06:00.359
And that would be
mr. Wild bill.

06:01.462 --> 06:02.427
<i> If you're looking</i>
<i> for information</i>

06:02.429 --> 06:03.795
<i> On fishing</i>
<i> south of the border,</i>

06:03.797 --> 06:05.330
There's only one man to call.

06:06.700 --> 06:08.700
<i> And he just finished</i>
<i> salmon tendering,</i>

06:08.702 --> 06:10.335
So we may catch him
in a good mood.

06:11.205 --> 06:12.704
Hop in, we're going to dutch.

06:14.108 --> 06:17.109
[tense music playing]

06:19.747 --> 06:23.115
[suspenseful music playing]

06:23.117 --> 06:24.216
[jeff] <i> where's josh at?</i>

06:25.419 --> 06:27.219
Josh is in seattle,
uh, you know,

06:27.221 --> 06:29.121
His got his brother shane
with him.

06:29.123 --> 06:31.123
They kind of wanna go

06:31.125 --> 06:33.225
Explore different things
and see if they can figure out

06:33.227 --> 06:36.528
Some other options
for something to do
in the future.

06:36.530 --> 06:39.965
We support josh in whatever
direction he wants to go,

06:40.000 --> 06:42.200
But for me and casey,

06:42.202 --> 06:44.836
Our priority is rebuilding
this market

06:44.905 --> 06:46.605
Over here in hawaii.

06:46.607 --> 06:48.573
So we're kind of concentrating
on this area,

06:48.575 --> 06:51.209
And hopefully land
some accounts.

06:51.211 --> 06:53.345
Nainoa's born and raised
in kailua-kona, hawaii,

06:53.447 --> 06:55.514
And he's been fishing here
his whole life.

06:55.516 --> 06:56.615
He's plugged in.

06:56.617 --> 06:59.050
He knows exactly who's buying
right now in kona.

07:02.356 --> 07:05.157
There's a tournament
coming up this weekend
you might find interesting.

07:06.427 --> 07:07.959
It's hosted by keoni llanes,

07:08.028 --> 07:09.861
It might be a good opportunity
to get in it.

07:09.897 --> 07:12.230
Keoni llanes,
why does that sound familiar?

07:12.232 --> 07:13.198
It's a really good family,

07:13.200 --> 07:14.599
Really respected family
over here,

07:14.601 --> 07:16.101
Especially in kona.

07:16.103 --> 07:17.602
He has a couple restaurants

07:17.604 --> 07:19.404
With a couple
different locations.

07:19.406 --> 07:21.640
-Really?
-Mmm-hmm.

07:21.708 --> 07:22.941
[casey] why don't we go
to this tournament?

07:22.943 --> 07:24.109
Try to get some face time
with him?

07:25.712 --> 07:26.845
I think there's a right way
to do things

07:26.947 --> 07:28.246
And a wrong way to do things.

07:28.315 --> 07:30.048
And the hawaiian way
to do things.

07:30.050 --> 07:31.516
You just said the
casey way of doing things.

07:31.518 --> 07:33.418
-Oh.
-[laughter]

07:38.926 --> 07:41.927
[tense music playing]

07:45.199 --> 07:47.599
[josh] <i> my whole life,</i>
<i> I've been coming up here,</i>

07:47.601 --> 07:50.602
<i> And I've never once went</i>
<i> out to fish for black bass.</i>

07:51.305 --> 07:52.537
[bill] <i> I mean, wherever I go</i>

07:52.539 --> 07:54.773
<i> I try to find something</i>
<i> to catch, you know.</i>

07:54.775 --> 07:57.042
If this works out good,
we can talk about the old man

07:57.143 --> 07:58.810
And catch some fish
in the meantime.

08:00.013 --> 08:02.013
[narrator] <i> captain</i>
<i> "wild bill" wichrowski.</i>

08:03.217 --> 08:05.317
<i> Living legend</i>
<i> on the bering sea.</i>

08:05.319 --> 08:07.419
Deuce and a quarter,
deuce and a quarter.

08:09.823 --> 08:12.457
[wild bill speaking].

08:12.526 --> 08:15.026
I called 2 and a quarter
and its 235.

08:15.028 --> 08:17.128
He's crabbing these waters
for 40 years

08:17.130 --> 08:18.530
And he knew my dad well.

08:18.532 --> 08:19.831
Do you know
how to speak english?

08:19.933 --> 08:23.201
[speaking spanish]

08:23.203 --> 08:25.103
[narrator] <i> not to mention,</i>
<i> he's lived in mexico</i>

08:25.105 --> 08:28.306
<i> For the past two decades</i>
<i> on his off time.</i>

08:28.308 --> 08:30.041
<i> If anybody could shed light</i>
<i> on my dad's plans,</i>

08:30.043 --> 08:31.510
It's gonna be him.

08:35.415 --> 08:38.350
[bill] <i> so you're one</i>
<i> of the harris tribe, huh?</i>

08:38.418 --> 08:39.417
We have the same mom.

08:39.419 --> 08:40.218
I got you.

08:41.955 --> 08:44.089
Well, it can't be all bad.

08:44.091 --> 08:45.757
[laughter]

08:45.859 --> 08:46.658
Maybe a half.

08:47.227 --> 08:48.827
[laughs]

08:48.829 --> 08:51.062
Phil harris, he was probably
one of the best fishermen

08:51.064 --> 08:52.263
I've ever met.

08:52.265 --> 08:55.500
And he never missed a chance
to put hooks in the water.

08:55.502 --> 08:58.436
<i> So josh wants to talk</i>
<i> about the past.</i>

08:58.538 --> 09:00.305
<i> I don't think there's</i>
<i> a better place to do it.</i>

09:01.408 --> 09:03.708
[tense music playing]

09:03.710 --> 09:04.676
All right, guys.

09:05.846 --> 09:08.513
There's a ton
of black bass out here,

09:08.515 --> 09:11.049
So run her down to the bottom,
and crank it up a little bit,

09:11.051 --> 09:12.751
And if you got multiple hooks,

09:12.819 --> 09:14.519
You wanna try
to get multiple fish.

09:16.323 --> 09:17.255
All right.

09:18.258 --> 09:19.024
[josh speaking]

09:21.128 --> 09:21.860
[bill] I'm in.

09:23.030 --> 09:24.696
Oh, [bleep].

09:24.698 --> 09:26.698
Bill's got that crazy look
in his eye.

09:27.935 --> 09:29.501
<i> There's a difference</i>
<i> between fishing and catchin'</i>

09:29.503 --> 09:31.603
[josh laughs] <i> come on.</i>

09:36.243 --> 09:38.610
[man] hey, man,
ready for the tournament?

09:38.612 --> 09:41.212
We're at keoni llanes'
fishing tournament today.

09:41.214 --> 09:44.049
Lots of good fishermen,
let's see what happens.

09:44.051 --> 09:45.417
Psyched to get up
and have a good time.

09:45.419 --> 09:46.818
It's gonna be fun.

09:46.820 --> 09:48.386
[dramatic music playing]

09:48.388 --> 09:50.622
[jeff] there's a little bit
of etiquette
when it comes to tournaments.

09:50.624 --> 09:52.357
Watch the brah's,
and the cuz's,

09:52.459 --> 09:53.491
And the shoots, okay?

09:53.493 --> 09:55.327
[casey] I don't use cuz,
we're good.

09:55.329 --> 09:56.928
Keoni's tournament is small,

09:56.930 --> 09:59.831
