<i> And hawaii.</i>

22:59.112 --> 23:01.712
It's been a long few days
to say the least.

23:01.714 --> 23:03.414
<i> But we came here</i>
<i> for a reason.</i>

23:03.416 --> 23:05.116
<i> If anybody knows</i>
<i> about my dad's time</i>

23:05.118 --> 23:06.450
In mexico or the gulf,

23:06.552 --> 23:07.718
It's gonna be wild bill.

23:09.622 --> 23:10.621
These are actually some charts

23:10.623 --> 23:12.656
That we found
in the old man's locker.

23:15.027 --> 23:16.460
[bill] yeah, I've been
all through here.

23:16.562 --> 23:18.462
-[josh] you have been?
-[bill] yeah.

23:18.564 --> 23:21.265
I mean, you got the gulf
and you got the atlantic.

23:21.333 --> 23:23.234
This is great fishing
through here.

23:23.335 --> 23:25.436
When we were out the other
day, you showed me a list.

23:25.505 --> 23:27.271
You know, mag bay, guadalupe.

23:27.273 --> 23:28.439
Yeah.

23:28.441 --> 23:30.941
Those are the hot spots
in the west coast, on baja.

23:31.010 --> 23:32.343
-[josh] okay.
-And that's a whole
different world.

23:32.445 --> 23:35.713
I mean, it's a completely
different fishery.

23:35.715 --> 23:37.648
You mean, it's a good
fishing spot or...

23:37.750 --> 23:38.782
It's tremendous.

23:38.784 --> 23:40.718
It's in the latitudes
where you have a lot of...

23:40.720 --> 23:44.655
Lot of currents that bring in
these nutrient-dense waters.

23:44.724 --> 23:46.624
I mean, that's why
it's big on tourism,

23:46.626 --> 23:48.726
That's why it's big
on sport fishing.

23:48.728 --> 23:49.727
In fact, it's...

23:49.729 --> 23:51.529
They're leaning way more

23:51.531 --> 23:53.063
Towards catch and release
over there.

23:54.434 --> 23:56.000
Yeah, we're selling, I mean,

23:56.002 --> 23:57.935
That doesn't mean
anything for us.

23:58.037 --> 23:59.804
Phil might've been
fishing tuna in mexico

23:59.806 --> 24:01.739
But between '80 and '86,

24:01.808 --> 24:03.040
There was an embargo.

24:03.910 --> 24:06.110
So basically,
mexican government

24:06.112 --> 24:07.745
Didn't want us, the americans,

24:07.814 --> 24:09.747
Harvesting tuna
in their waters.

24:09.816 --> 24:11.515
And obviously we didn't want
the mexicans

24:11.517 --> 24:13.050
Harvesting tuna in our waters.

24:13.052 --> 24:14.518
It's just like us
with crab and russia,

24:14.520 --> 24:15.519
You know, it's...
It was a war.

24:16.255 --> 24:17.822
It got pretty heated.

24:17.824 --> 24:19.523
So he couldn't have fished
for them?

24:20.693 --> 24:22.226
Not commercially for tuna.

24:22.228 --> 24:24.462
[tense music playing]

24:24.530 --> 24:26.130
[bill] you know unless he was
fishing mexican waters

24:26.132 --> 24:27.431
From somewhere else.

24:29.502 --> 24:30.234
I don't get it.

24:30.937 --> 24:31.902
Well, think about it.

24:32.672 --> 24:34.905
Your dad was down here
in the '80s.

24:34.907 --> 24:37.441
You know, he was in alabama,
by la batre,

24:37.543 --> 24:39.610
Working boats,
building a boat.

24:39.612 --> 24:41.045
If he was gonna fish,

24:41.047 --> 24:42.613
He would be fishing
in the gulf.

24:43.749 --> 24:45.916
Do you think
it would be over here

24:45.918 --> 24:47.351
Instead of over there?

24:47.453 --> 24:49.019
I would think
that if he was down there,

24:49.722 --> 24:51.055
I'll bet he was fishing.

24:52.825 --> 24:55.226
Finding out what my dad
was up to.

24:55.228 --> 24:56.927
I mean, that's one of the most
important things.

24:57.597 --> 24:59.129
I gotta figure this out.

25:00.500 --> 25:01.632
You're going to the gulf, man.

25:02.902 --> 25:04.401
[josh] <i> bayou la batre,</i>
<i> alabama.</i>

25:04.403 --> 25:06.704
<i> It's known</i>
<i> for shrimp, shipyards,</i>

25:06.706 --> 25:09.039
<i> But not big tuna.</i>

25:09.108 --> 25:10.941
Going there is a gamble
but it was also a gamble

25:11.043 --> 25:12.343
To build
the cornelia marie there.

25:12.411 --> 25:14.912
And that turned out
pretty damn good.

25:14.914 --> 25:17.915
Besides, it's one place I know
for sure the old man went.

25:25.424 --> 25:27.625
[tense music playing]

25:28.327 --> 25:30.060
[kalina] <i> you made it.</i>

25:30.129 --> 25:31.428
-[keoni] morning, sir.
-[casey] morning, bro.

25:33.799 --> 25:36.000
I appreciate your support
yesterday, man.

25:36.002 --> 25:37.801
I wanna go out there
and catch fish for my buddy.

25:37.803 --> 25:39.103
[kalina] for sure.

25:39.105 --> 25:41.138
There's one thing that
I've learned
growing up fishing,

25:41.240 --> 25:43.607
It's always do
what you say you're gonna do.

25:43.609 --> 25:45.943
And you have to finish
what you start.

25:46.045 --> 25:47.811
<i> I've got one day left</i>
<i> in this tournament,</i>

25:47.813 --> 25:49.313
<i> And I'm gonna make</i>
<i> the most of it.</i>

25:50.416 --> 25:51.348
<i> Let's go catch a fish,</i>
<i> all right?</i>

25:51.350 --> 25:52.349
[kalina] <i> yeah.</i>

25:55.555 --> 25:56.921
[jeff] <i> beautiful morning</i>
<i> out here.</i>

25:56.923 --> 25:58.122
<i> Sun coming up.</i>

25:58.691 --> 26:00.124
Wow, that's pretty cool.

26:02.795 --> 26:05.529
Maybe that's casey's buddy
kyle smiling down on 'em.

26:06.732 --> 26:08.532
<i> Day two, so we're gonna</i>
<i> give it a shot</i>

26:08.601 --> 26:09.800
And ready for a big one.

26:09.802 --> 26:11.235
Let's hang onto one today.

26:12.104 --> 26:13.304
[jeff] <i> yesterday, nainoa and</i>

26:13.306 --> 26:14.538
<i> Didn't end up</i>
<i> catching anything.</i>

26:14.607 --> 26:17.041
And the day ended up
getting cut short.

26:17.142 --> 26:19.443
So we've gotta produce
to have a shot
in this tournament

26:19.545 --> 26:21.011
<i> And get the rest</i>
<i> of the 800 pounds</i>

26:21.013 --> 26:22.613
<i> That we need</i>
<i> to send to kauai.</i>

26:24.750 --> 26:26.317
We went south yesterday,

26:26.319 --> 26:29.019
So today we're fishing
a little bit more north.

26:29.021 --> 26:30.554
And, uh, we're fishing
a little bit deeper

26:30.623 --> 26:32.323
On the thousand.

26:32.325 --> 26:35.059
They call it the thousand
because it's a thousand
fathoms deep,

26:35.061 --> 26:37.628
The contour of the island
is very steep.

26:37.630 --> 26:39.930
<i> It drops off really quick.</i>

26:39.932 --> 26:41.298
Today it seems productive
and a lot of it

26:41.300 --> 26:43.300
Is because we see birds
flying around

26:43.302 --> 26:45.402
<i> And so, you know, we'll jus</i>
<i> kinda stick with it,</i>

26:45.404 --> 26:47.204
Wait for one of these guys
to bite.

26:48.474 --> 26:49.740
<i> You know, pressure's on.</i>

26:53.546 --> 26:55.312
I see some splashes
over there.

26:55.314 --> 26:56.246
Check that out.

27:01.020 --> 27:02.553
[beeps]

27:02.655 --> 27:04.054
[jeff] so, we just marked
a fish right here.

27:04.590 --> 27:06.523
[beeping]

27:06.525 --> 27:07.825
[nainoa] [bleep] going nuts.

27:08.461 --> 27:11.362
[tense music playing]

27:11.463 --> 27:12.563
Oh, right there.

27:12.631 --> 27:13.631
Hooked up.

27:15.034 --> 27:15.933
[nainoa] oh, it's a huge one.

27:16.002 --> 27:17.134
Oh, a big blow up.

27:17.603 --> 27:18.802
[beeping]

27:19.505 --> 27:20.704
[jeff] oh, man.

27:21.741 --> 27:22.740
We got a big pile
of mahi-mahis

27:22.808 --> 27:23.941
Behind the boat right now.

27:26.045 --> 27:27.044
[nainoa] yeah, yeah.

27:28.014 --> 27:29.013
Here we go.

27:29.849 --> 27:30.914
We're in it.

27:32.718 --> 27:34.151
Another one.

27:34.253 --> 27:38.422
Mahi-mahi, they're good,
13 to 17 pounders.

27:38.424 --> 27:40.224
And a situation like this,
you gotta try

27:40.226 --> 27:41.692
And keep 'em behind the boat
as long as you can

27:41.694 --> 27:43.527
Because you don't know
how long they're gonna stay.

27:44.030 --> 27:45.029
Got one on.

27:47.700 --> 27:49.199
Oh, my god.

27:51.303 --> 27:52.036
Another one on.

27:52.605 --> 27:53.504
All right. Here it comes.

27:53.506 --> 27:54.538
[jeff] I got 'em.

27:56.809 --> 27:57.808
[nainoa] nice fish, man.

28:00.846 --> 28:02.713
<i> Awesome one, man.</i>
<i> Awesome.</i>

28:03.949 --> 28:05.916
We're gonna hang here.
This is the spot.

28:05.918 --> 28:07.351
Just gonna hang out
right out front...

28:07.420 --> 28:08.152
The front door.

28:08.220 --> 28:10.254
[seagulls squawking]

28:11.524 --> 28:13.223
So I think we just stay
out front in...

28:13.225 --> 28:15.859
Between keauhou
and captain cook monument

28:15.928 --> 28:17.361
And just work this area.

28:17.430 --> 28:19.730
Maybe get better luck out here
on the big game.

28:19.732 --> 28:20.664
[casey] sounds good.

28:20.733 --> 28:21.598
I saw life there yesterday.

28:21.600 --> 28:22.900
Maybe they're still around.

28:24.303 --> 28:26.704
<i> Hopefully it's the biting</i>
<i> kind of life today.</i>

28:26.706 --> 28:29.640
<i> There's no doubt that</i>
<i> we're behind in poundage</i>
<i> right now.</i>

28:29.709 --> 28:31.642
We only caught a few
mahi-mahi yesterday.

28:31.711 --> 28:32.943
If we're gonna win,

28:32.945 --> 28:34.511
We're gonna have to hook
something a lot bigger.

28:36.215 --> 28:37.614
You got anything
you wanna run today?

28:38.217 --> 28:39.450
Uh...

28:40.720 --> 28:42.653
Just probably like a jet
or a bullet or something.

28:42.755 --> 28:43.454
Yeah.

28:43.555 --> 28:44.955
[keoni] yeah.

28:44.957 --> 28:45.723
You got it, man.

28:45.725 --> 28:46.623
[casey] oh.

28:46.625 --> 28:48.058
Here we go. We're on, guys.

28:48.127 --> 28:49.126
[reeling stops]

28:50.262 --> 28:51.228
[bleep].

28:52.064 --> 28:53.063
We were on.

28:56.802 --> 28:57.801
I think we lost it.

28:57.803 --> 28:59.636
Oh.

28:59.705 --> 29:01.605
-[keoni speaking]
-[casey] had the drag set
too light, I think,

29:01.607 --> 29:03.073
Or he spit it out,

29:03.075 --> 29:05.209
Whatever it was, but he took
some line there,

29:05.211 --> 29:06.944
We gotta get this thing back
in the water right away.

29:06.946 --> 29:08.412
Do you have any other
live bait rods ready?

29:08.414 --> 29:09.213
[keoni] yeah.

29:09.215 --> 29:12.549
[tense music playing]

29:14.820 --> 29:16.019
There's gotta be
another fish here,

29:16.021 --> 29:17.921
Where it's gonna feed out
a live bait here.

29:20.860 --> 29:22.726
Feel 'em kick
in there a little.

29:22.728 --> 29:23.861
When you see 'em
fluttering like that,

29:23.929 --> 29:25.529
It means something's around
that's eyeballing them,

29:25.531 --> 29:26.830
They saw something
they don't like.

29:29.502 --> 29:30.834
He's getting a little nervous.

29:34.640 --> 29:35.806
-[reel whirring]
-there he goes.

29:35.808 --> 29:37.841
We're on. Oh, we're on.

29:37.910 --> 29:39.142
Holy [bleep].

29:39.144 --> 29:40.944
Yeah, we're on. Look at
the way that thing's flying.

29:41.647 --> 29:42.813
We're on here.

29:44.049 --> 29:45.048
Wow.

29:45.718 --> 29:47.050
That's a big fish.

29:47.052 --> 29:48.619
Casey, what's it doing, man?

29:51.624 --> 29:52.356
Oh, there he is.

29:52.925 --> 29:54.324
You see him right there?

29:54.326 --> 29:56.727
They're smelling what
we're selling today, guys.

30:01.934 --> 30:02.933
Gotta be a marlin.

30:03.602 --> 30:04.301
[keoni] oh, there he is.

30:05.337 --> 30:07.037
You see him right there?

30:07.039 --> 30:10.407
They're smelling what
we're selling today, guys.

30:10.409 --> 30:13.110
<i> I've got my first big pelagi</i>
<i> of the tournament on the hoo</i>

30:13.112 --> 30:15.245
And a potential client
watching every move.

30:16.415 --> 30:18.215
<i> I'm trying to land</i>
<i> more than just a fish here.</i>

30:21.954 --> 30:23.554
Casey, what's it doing, man?

30:23.622 --> 30:24.922
Pulling tight.

30:24.924 --> 30:26.323
-Straight that way.
-Okay.

30:28.627 --> 30:29.726
[casey] as the boat dips here,

30:31.030 --> 30:32.462
We're cranking.

30:32.531 --> 30:33.931
Pull up, it pulls the fish up,

30:33.933 --> 30:35.165
It's basically like pulling up
on the rod,

30:35.201 --> 30:36.600
We're just letting
the boat do the work.

30:38.537 --> 30:40.504
I think this is it, guys.

30:40.506 --> 30:42.639
Assuming nobody else catches
something bigger today.

30:43.042 --> 30:44.041
Turning.

30:44.944 --> 30:46.009
[keoni] turning.

30:47.513 --> 30:48.545
[casey] he's going
that way now.

30:49.915 --> 30:52.549
He's not happy...
Yeah, that's a nice fish.

30:52.651 --> 30:53.450
-[kalina] yup.
-[keoni] yup.

30:54.720 --> 30:55.619
We're getting close.

30:55.621 --> 30:57.054
I see color, man. Right here.

30:57.056 --> 30:59.223
[tense music playing]

30:59.225 --> 31:00.824
Oh, yeah. He's comin' up.

31:00.826 --> 31:02.960
[kalina] oh, he's a nice fish.

31:02.962 --> 31:05.362
I'd say it's what?
250, 300-pound fish?

31:05.430 --> 31:07.130
[keoni] that's what it
looks like.

31:07.132 --> 31:09.233
[casey] he's right here,
get a gaff ready.

31:09.334 --> 31:10.367
[keoni] yup.

31:10.369 --> 31:11.702
[casey] never seen
a real artist in action, yet.

31:11.704 --> 31:13.303
-[keoni laughs]
-[casey] that's it.

31:16.709 --> 31:17.808
Yeah.

31:17.810 --> 31:18.809
Got a second gaff?

31:20.546 --> 31:21.545
[casey] ready?

31:21.647 --> 31:23.013
[keoni] on three,
up and over on this side.

31:23.015 --> 31:25.115
-One, two, three.
-Two, three.

31:25.451 --> 31:26.350
[grunts]

31:27.319 --> 31:28.318
[casey] watch out the bill.

31:29.955 --> 31:30.954
-Woo!
-[kalina] woo!

31:31.023 --> 31:32.556
Good job guys! [laughs]

31:32.625 --> 31:33.857
There it is.

31:33.926 --> 31:35.859
-Yeah.
-Yeah. [bleep].

31:36.629 --> 31:38.262
[laughs]

31:39.331 --> 31:40.931
Oh, [bleep].

31:40.933 --> 31:42.199
[casey] oh, my god.

31:42.201 --> 31:43.233
[kalina] holy [bleep].

31:43.302 --> 31:44.434
That one's for kyle.

31:45.037 --> 31:46.203
Thank you, keoni.

31:46.939 --> 31:49.139
Wow, what a fish.

31:49.241 --> 31:51.608
Catching a marlin this size
never gets old

31:51.610 --> 31:53.210
No matter how often you do it.

31:54.313 --> 31:56.013
<i> And it puts us in the runnin</i>
<i> to win this thing.</i>

31:59.151 --> 31:59.950
[beeps]

32:02.988 --> 32:05.222
[nainoa] oh,
big ahi right there.

32:05.224 --> 32:07.157
Huge ahi, look at that,

32:07.225 --> 32:08.859
Big explosion on the surface
right there,

32:10.029 --> 32:10.961
Nice white water.

32:11.964 --> 32:13.964
We got fish jumping
around the boat,

32:13.966 --> 32:15.198
So, you know,

32:15.200 --> 32:17.034
We know the fish
are in the area.

32:19.605 --> 32:20.504
[rod whirring]

32:21.941 --> 32:22.973
We're on.

32:25.511 --> 32:27.110
Nice and tight.
Straight down, right now.

32:27.112 --> 32:28.211
It's pumping, so...

32:29.949 --> 32:31.114
It feels like a nice ahi.

32:32.418 --> 32:33.951
[suspenseful music playing]

32:34.019 --> 32:35.052
[jeff] we're gonna switch.

32:36.088 --> 32:37.821
It feels like
a really good-sized fish.

32:37.823 --> 32:39.656
We're just being patient
with him.

32:39.725 --> 32:41.124
There's no sense
trying to muscle him.

32:42.127 --> 32:44.194
It's actually better
to keep the fish down deep

32:44.196 --> 32:46.229
Because the water is cooler,

32:46.231 --> 32:49.199
So that way the body
temperature of the fish
will stay cooler.

32:49.201 --> 32:51.601
If you keep the fish high
and he gives you a hard time,

32:51.603 --> 32:53.003
You know, a lot of
times that's how your fish

32:53.005 --> 32:54.805
Can become what we call
brown burn.

32:56.041 --> 32:57.107
The meat will look like
its bruised

32:57.109 --> 32:58.608
Or it's even been cooked,

32:58.610 --> 33:01.044
So all we can do
is just be patient,

33:01.113 --> 33:02.746
Play it slow and get this guy.

33:05.150 --> 33:06.850
We should see color here
any second.

33:15.761 --> 33:16.760
Nice fish.

33:19.031 --> 33:20.130
[nainoa] all right.

33:20.132 --> 33:21.598
-Nice, pal. Good job man.
-Nice fish, pal.

33:21.600 --> 33:22.332
Good job.

33:23.002 --> 33:24.301
Looks about 140.

33:25.304 --> 33:26.703
Beautiful fish.

33:26.705 --> 33:28.138
<i> We signed up</i>
<i> for this tournament</i>

33:28.207 --> 33:29.506
To make inroads with keoni.

33:29.508 --> 33:31.742
Drum up some business
and knock out this order

33:31.810 --> 33:33.710
<i> For taylor at the same time</i>

33:33.712 --> 33:35.112
But it's still a competition

33:35.114 --> 33:36.413
And I don't like losing.

33:37.249 --> 33:38.749
We're on the board.

33:38.850 --> 33:40.717
Try to get another one,
that's the plan.

33:42.121 --> 33:43.253
Tournament's not over.

33:45.290 --> 33:48.325
[seagulls squawking]

33:52.631 --> 33:53.530
[josh] <i> all right. Let's go.</i>

33:53.532 --> 33:54.664
[shane] <i> all right, man.</i>

33:55.834 --> 33:56.733
[bill] josh.

33:57.936 --> 33:59.102
Dude.

33:59.104 --> 34:00.704
I did some thinking and...

34:01.774 --> 34:04.508
If I can actually help you
guys figure this out

34:04.510 --> 34:05.609
What the old man was doing,

34:05.611 --> 34:07.611
-I'll give you a hint.
-Really?

34:07.613 --> 34:09.012
I could streamline this
for you a lot.

34:09.014 --> 34:10.714
I know a bunch of people
down there and...

34:10.716 --> 34:12.149
Dude, that's great news.

34:12.217 --> 34:13.150
[bill] it should be good.

34:13.251 --> 34:14.484
I looked at it and I think
I can pull it off.

34:14.486 --> 34:16.053
Dude, you have no clue
how big of a help
that's gonna be.

34:16.121 --> 34:17.320
[bill] no, it'll be good.

34:17.322 --> 34:18.588
I'd like to see
what he was doing too.

34:18.590 --> 34:20.524
-It's... I'm curious.
-Yeah.

34:20.526 --> 34:22.159
<i> One of the benefits</i>
<i> for having a career</i>

34:22.227 --> 34:24.861
That spans four decades,

34:24.930 --> 34:26.396
You make a lot of connection

34:26.398 --> 34:28.832
And phil was a friend of mine.

34:28.901 --> 34:31.401
<i> If I can help josh</i>
<i> with his business,</i>

34:31.403 --> 34:33.603
<i> Connect him with a piece</i>
<i> of phil's past,</i>

34:33.605 --> 34:35.505
That's not a bad days' work.

34:35.507 --> 34:37.607
Even for an old cranky
[bleep] like me.

34:37.609 --> 34:39.509
[laughs]

34:39.511 --> 34:40.911
Yeah. There's only
one rule for me.

